review_blob: Bottle. Ruby body with light head. Low carbonated. Mildly bitter palate with tones of chocolate and toffee.
Tap in Lucerna Hospoda, Prague. Clear amber body, light white head. Low carbonated. Aroma is very light, fruity and corn. Tastes light with tones of cereal and flowers.
Very dark ruby, almost black body. Light brown head. Medium carbonated. Aromas include strong coffee, smoke and some bread. Mild in taste, ever slightly sour with bittersweet accent.
Dark brown, almost black body. Brown head. Medium carbonated. Intense aroma, with chocolate, coffee and dried plum tones.Tastes slightly burned bread. Overall is a very decent porter.
Dark cherry in colour. Light brown foam almost instantly dissapearing. Medium rye bread aroma. Sweet aftertaste.
